title: Florida Firm Recalls Chicken Wrap Products Due To Possible Listeria Monocytogenes Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, July 27, 2012 - LSG Sky Chefs, an Orlando, Fla. establishment, is recalling approximately 735 pounds of ready-to-eat chipotle chicken wrap products. The products contain diced onions that are the subject of a Food and Drug Administration (FDA) recall due to possible Listeria monocytogenes...
